`lib/saga_map/rendering/saga_map_painter.dart:77-78`:
```dart
bool shouldRepaint(covariant SagaMapPainter oldDelegate) =>
    oldDelegate.scene != scene;
```
`SagaScene` (`saga_scene.dart`) has no `==`/`hashCode` override, and `buildSagaScene` (`saga_scene_builder.dart:13`) constructs a **brand-new** `SagaScene` every call. So `!=` is identity comparison on a value that's never the same object twice â€” `shouldRepaint` always returns `true`, even when `progress`/`currentLevel` haven't changed and the frame is visually identical. This is exactly the React "new object reference every render defeats `React.memo`" bug, just in `CustomPainter` form. It'll cause every rebuild to trigger a full repaint of every visible stone once the screen is actually wired up.

Fix: give the scene graph value equality, reusing the pattern already in `SagaMapState` (rung 2 â€” copy what's already in the codebase, don't invent a new convention):

```dart
// saga_node.dart
@override
bool operator ==(Object other) =>
    other is SagaNode &&
    index == other.index && x == other.x && depth == other.depth && state == other.state;
@override
int get hashCode => Object.hash(index, x, depth, state);
```
```dart
// perspective_projector.dart (ProjectedNode)
@override
bool operator ==(Object other) =>
    other is ProjectedNode &&
    node == other.node && screenX == other.screenX &&
    screenY == other.screenY && scale == other.scale && fogFactor == other.fogFactor;
@override
int get hashCode => Object.hash(node, screenX, screenY, scale, fogFactor);
```
```dart
// visible_node_window.dart
@override
bool operator ==(Object other) =>
    other is VisibleNodeWindow && start == other.start && end == other.end;
@override
int get hashCode => Object.hash(start, end);
```
```dart
// saga_scene.dart
import 'package:flutter/foundation.dart' show listEquals;
...
@override
bool operator ==(Object other) =>
    other is SagaScene && window == other.window && listEquals(nodes, other.nodes);
@override
int get hashCode => Object.hash(window, Object.hashAll(nodes));
```
`listEquals` is already reachable via `flutter/foundation.dart` â†’ no new dependency (rung 3, stdlib/SDK covers it).

